# IaC surface — when you touch infrastructure-as-code

Loads on Terraform/Pulumi/CDK/Crossplane/infra module paths. Opt-in depth: app-only repos
without these folders never see this rule. For apply runbooks use **`ops-deploy`**; for
workflow YAML use **`ci-pipeline`**; for module/state design use **`infra-iac`**.

## Before writing
- Run (or confirm) **`infra-iac`**: blast radius, remote state+lock, IAM/secrets, plan/apply
  approval, stateful protection, rollback.
- Reuse existing backend/module layout — second state pattern is a consistency stop.

## While implementing
- No secrets in git (`tfvars`, env files, kubeconfigs).
- Prefer OIDC / short-lived creds over static keys.
- Protect stateful resources from casual destroy.

## Before claiming done
- Prod: plan reviewed + approval path named; rollback noted; link **`ops-deploy`** if
  applying to a live env in the same change.
